<paragraph id="F9405D061A35F46D3DD14D071D7BFDB6" blockId="37.[151,1436,152,663]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis id="CB8B81141A35F46D3DD14D071D94FDDD" bold="true" box="[196,466,525,551]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">General distribution:</emphasis>
This is a southern species ranging from eastern 
<collectingRegion id="3B3B93E41A35F46D390D4D0718E4FDDD" box="[1048,1186,525,551]" country="United States of America" name="New Jersey" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">New Jersey</collectingRegion>
south to 
<collectingRegion id="3B3B93E41A35F46D38064D07192FFDDD" box="[1299,1385,525,551]" country="United States of America" name="Florida" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Florida</collectingRegion>
and west to 
<collectingRegion id="3B3B93E41A35F46D3DE74D381D7CFDB6" box="[242,314,562,588]" country="United States of America" name="Texas" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Texas</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F9405D061A35F46D3DD14D5D1F44FD6D" blockId="37.[151,1436,152,663]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis id="CB8B81141A35F46D3DD14D5D1D2CFD8B" bold="true" box="[196,362,599,625]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Larval hosts:</emphasis>
Larvae obtained from eggs were reared on orchardgrass (
<taxonomicName id="3EFF26851A35F46D39094D521946FD8B" box="[1052,1280,600,625]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Dactylis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glomerata">
<emphasis id="CB8B81141A35F46D39094D521946FD8B" box="[1052,1280,600,625]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Dactylis glomerata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L., 
<taxonomicName id="3EFF26851A35F46D38274D5219D2FD88" authorityName="Barnhart" authorityYear="1895" baseAuthorityName="R.Br." box="[1330,1428,600,626]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Poaceae</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="9D6E20F71A35F46D3D8B4D771D0EFD6D" author="Godfrey, G. L." box="[158,328,637,663]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" pagination="1 - 265" refId="ref30677" refString="Godfrey, G. L. (1972) A review and reclassification of larvae of the subfamily Hadeninae (Lepidoptera, Noctuidae) of American north of Mexico. U. S. Department of Agriculture Technical Bulletin, 1450, 1 - 265." type="journal article" year="1972">Godfrey 1972</bibRefCitation>
), but probably feeds on other grasses.
</paragraph>
